    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, i'm working on a dataset where one feature is 'annual income' (ranging from 20k to 500k) and another is 'age' (ranging from 18 to 80). why do i actually need to do feature scaling or normalization before feeding this into a model instead of just leaving it as is?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Feature scaling is crucial because models like neural networks and support vector machines rely on distance calculations, which become biased when income (50x the scale of age) dominates the learning process. Without normalization, the model might incorrectly prioritize the high-magnitude feature, leading to slower convergence or suboptimal performance. Additionally, data preprocessing techniques often require inputs to be within a specific range, such as [0, 1], to function efficiently.",
      "source": "target",
