      "content": "That's exactly right! You are essentially putting all features on an equal playing field so the learning algorithm isn't distracted by one specific dimension dominating the others. By scaling the data, you're transforming their visual geometry in the model's \"weight space\" so that minimizing the error looks like a smooth ball rolling down a hill rather than a chaotic tennis ball spinning in a funnel. This ensures the model learns from the actual relationships within the data rather than just the raw magnitude of the numbers.",
